A: The issue is that you're calling dataSnapshot.getChildren().iterator().next() in the loop. This means that you're always getting the first child of the snapshot, regardless of the current child in the loop.
You should instead use dataSnapshot1.getValue(String.class) to get the value of the current child in the loop.
Here's the corrected code:
rootRef.addValueEventListener(new ValueEventListener() {
    @Override
    public void onDataChange(DataSnapshot dataSnapshot) {
        for (DataSnapshot dataSnapshot1:dataSnapshot.getChildren()) {
            i = i + 1;
            names.add(dataSnapshot1.getValue(String.class));
        }
        Toast.makeText(signup.this,""+names,Toast.LENGTH_LONG).show();
    }

    @Override
    public void onCancelled(DatabaseError databaseError) {
        // Handle the error
    }
});

This code will add all the values of the children to the names list.

